## 14. Key Equations Summary

### 14.1 Two-Temperature Model

**Electron energy**:
$$C_e(T_e) \frac{\partial T_e}{\partial t} = \nabla \cdot [k_e(T_e) \nabla T_e] - G(T_e)(T_e - T_l) + q̇_{laser}$$

**Lattice energy**:
$$C_l \frac{\partial T_l}{\partial t} = \nabla \cdot (k_l \nabla T_l) + G(T_e)(T_e - T_l) - q̇_{phase} - q̇_{gas-metal}$$

### 14.2 Phase-Change Relations

**Saturation pressure**:
$$p_{sat}(T_l) = p_{ref} \exp\left[\frac{L_v}{R}\left(\frac{1}{T_{vap}} - \frac{1}{T_l}\right)\right]$$

**Mass flux (Hertz-Knudsen)**:
$$j = \alpha_e \sqrt{\frac{1}{2\pi R T_l}} \, p_{sat}(T_l)$$

**Recoil pressure (Knight)**:
$$p_{recoil} = \frac{2 - \beta_m}{2\alpha_e} \cdot j \sqrt{2\pi R T_l}$$

### 14.3 VOF Transport

**Phase fraction evolution**:
$$\frac{\partial \alpha}{\partial t} + \nabla \cdot (\mathbf{u} \alpha) + \nabla \cdot [c_\alpha |\mathbf{u}_r| \mathbf{n} \alpha(1-\alpha)] = S_\alpha$$

### 14.4 Momentum Equation

$$\frac{\partial (\rho \mathbf{u})}{\partial t} + \nabla \cdot (\rho \mathbf{u} \mathbf{u}) = -\nabla p + \nabla \cdot [\mu(\nabla \mathbf{u} + \nabla \mathbf{u}^T)] + \rho \mathbf{g} + \mathbf{F}_{recoil} + \mathbf{F}_{surface}$$

where:
- **Frecoil** = precoil |∇αmetal| **n** (recoil body force)
- **Fsurface** = σκ∇αmetal (capillary force)

